transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Hi there, how are you?

Speaker 1: Good, thank you for asking.

Speaker 2: Good, is Tamara there?

Speaker 1: No.

Speaker 2: Let me place you on brief hold, let me see if I can help you as well, if you want.

Speaker 1: Sure, sure.

Speaker 2: I thought that I had canceled my prescription like a month ago, maybe two,

Speaker 1: and I see that I was charged again for another round.

Speaker 2: And I texted her, she texted me back and told me it's best to call, so I'm calling.

Speaker 1: Okay, yes, absolutely.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so Mr. Ferreri?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay, yes, so I see that, yes, you have a prescription for Viagra and tablet,

Speaker 1: and you paused your prescription for six months, that's why you were up for a refill.

Speaker 2: I mean, you could pause for another six months, or you don't want to get to refill in six months later?

Speaker 1: No.

Speaker 2: Yeah, at the time I told the guy to not put, he said, when I spoke to him six months ago,

Speaker 1: I told him that I wanted to cancel, and he said, well, why don't you just pause it for six months,

Speaker 2: and then we'll contact you before we resubscribe it.

Speaker 1: And it looked like I was charged anyway, so I just want to cancel it altogether.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah, just be advised in the future if you try to reorder,

Speaker 2: because I'm going to cancel the prescription for Dr. Williams that you have here,

Speaker 1: and since there is a cost, in the future they're going to have to pay that again for you,

Speaker 2: if they take the order, so you're going to have a different price.

Speaker 1: So don't be surprised if you try to order 10 pills and the price is different.

Speaker 2: Usually they advise to pause, get 10 pills once or twice a year to lock your price in,

Speaker 1: and keep kind of access to your Viagra and stuff like that.

Speaker 2: But if you're sure that you will not need Viagra in the future and all of that,

Speaker 1: I'm canceling the account, okay?

Speaker 2: Yeah, let's do that, please.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: So you all said Mr. Ferreri and everything are being canceled for you.

Speaker 1: You will not receive any refill moving forward, and you all said.

Speaker 2: Okay, are they going to – did they send out the prescription?

Speaker 1: Yes, the last refill I shipped.

Speaker 2: You probably, if there's a delay, you don't have a tracking number,

Speaker 1: you will see that in your email, but, yeah, I shipped already.

Speaker 2: Okay, well, can I return it for a refund, or how does this work?

Speaker 1: Yeah, you can write refuse return to the sender for a refund, or if you want,

Speaker 2: I can ask my manager to get you a discount as we speak, whatever works best for you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, either way.

Speaker 2: Either way is fine.

Speaker 1: Okay, so let me place you on brief hold, and I'm going to ask to see if I can get you a discount.

Speaker 2: Okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.
